    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship: you can start and bid 2-3 but beware of the captain and choose to go fist. the fellowship is made up to survive and double. i chose boromir instead of faramir because i think he is a better fighter but just in case i threw faramir in for a splash or a stooge. bounder is to help frodo and might of nemenor heals up the companions if i get lucky. <br />
<br />
Shadow: the shadow is designed to kill and or stop the opponent from doubling. i know you might think uruks suck but if you think about it they pretty much have everything to counter. brought back alive is to kill the merry and pippin in either merry&#39;s sword or DH deck. saruman is a good minion here because he can assign the large minions to hurt the exhausted companions. and greed punishes large fellowships.<br />
